1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,180
Good afternoon, mister Patel.

2
00:00:02,180 --> 00:00:05,000
This is Gina from the HR department.

3
00:00:05,080 --> 00:00:09,959
I wanted to go over some details about your recent travel reimbursement request.

4
00:00:10,040 --> 00:00:14,759
I understand you were attending the Tech Innovations Conference in Berlin last month.

5
00:00:15,295 --> 00:00:20,255
Thank you for submitting the receipts for your flights, lodging, and meals.

6
00:00:20,255 --> 00:00:24,334
However, there seems to be an issue with one of the hotel charges.

7
00:00:24,255 --> 00:00:28,411
Our company policy covers only up to $150 per night,

8
00:00:28,411 --> 00:00:31,030
and it looks like your hotel exceeded that.

9
00:00:31,030 --> 00:00:33,470
Let's meet in person to clarify things.

10
00:00:33,470 --> 00:00:37,110
Could you drop by my office tomorrow afternoon around 3PM?

11
00:00:37,110 --> 00:00:39,410
That way, we can settle everything quickly.

12
00:00:39,490 --> 00:00:40,529
Thanks.

13
00:00:42,210 --> 00:00:44,015
Hello, mister Robson.

14
00:00:44,015 --> 00:00:50,115
This is June Brown, your financial adviser, calling about your investment portfolio review.

15
00:00:50,115 --> 00:00:52,958
I was looking over the account details you provided,

16
00:00:52,958 --> 00:00:56,110
and I noticed that some information is missing.

17
00:00:56,110 --> 00:01:02,729
Specifically, I don't have the latest updates on the income and valuations from your real estate investments.

18
00:01:02,809 --> 00:01:08,889
These details are the missing pieces of the puzzle for a complete analysis of your financial situation.

19
00:01:09,205 --> 00:01:15,044
Could you please email me the recent appraisals and income statements from your rental properties?

20
00:01:14,965 --> 00:01:20,244
I won't be able to finalize the review of your investment portfolio without them.

21
00:01:22,580 --> 00:01:30,899
Welcome, everyone, to this orientation session for our institute's certification course in graphic design.

22
00:01:30,820 --> 00:01:34,979
I'm Alex Martin, your instructor for the next few weeks.

23
00:01:35,055 --> 00:01:38,574
Before we begin, I have some news to share.

24
00:01:38,575 --> 00:01:47,135
Once you complete the course, you'll each have the opportunity to have a one on one session with a career adviser at no additional cost.

25
00:01:47,250 --> 00:01:52,129
It's a wonderful benefit for you all, so I encourage you to make use of it.

26
00:01:52,370 --> 00:01:55,630
Now let's begin our first session.

27
00:01:55,630 --> 00:02:01,809
Please log in to our training system using the username and password provided on your name tags.

28
00:02:04,375 --> 00:02:08,074
Floyd, it seems there's an issue with your project report from last week.

29
00:02:08,074 --> 00:02:08,894
Oh, really?

30
00:02:08,894 --> 00:02:09,914
What's the problem?

31
00:02:09,914 --> 00:02:15,894
Diana from the quality control team mentioned that the report lacks the required detailed analysis for the third quarter.

32
00:02:16,200 --> 00:02:17,519
That's strange.

33
00:02:17,519 --> 00:02:21,000
I remember including that analysis, but I'll check it again.

34
00:02:21,240 --> 00:02:22,140
Okay.

35
00:02:22,140 --> 00:02:24,840
In the meantime, you'll need to draft an updated version.

36
00:02:24,989 --> 00:02:29,169
Normally, Diana handles this, but she's on a training course with James right now.

37
00:02:29,169 --> 00:02:33,588
You should reach out to the project coordinator to find out who can review the updated report.

38
00:02:33,588 --> 00:02:34,449
Got it.

39
00:02:34,449 --> 00:02:35,909
I'll take care of it right away.
